<subSubSection id="C331C195B74BFFF4FAC8F33EFE64F785" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="120" pageId="12" pageNumber="119" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B94921EB74BFFF4FAC8F33EFE64F785" blockId="12.[1377,2583,2575,3277]" lastBlockId="13.[185,1403,286,3079]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="120" pageId="12" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="B95F4E0CB74BFFF5FAC8F33EF997FAF8" bold="true" box="[1379,1628,3205,3238]" pageId="12" pageNumber="119">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 430-440 mm, tail 33-39 mm, ear 45-52 mm, hindfoot 89-94 mm; weight 1.1-6 kg. The Marsh Rabbit is small to medium-sized, with rough hair. Dorsal fur, rump, uppertail, and hindlegs vary from chestnut-brown to dark rusty red. Ventral fur is reddish brown, and nape is dark rufous cinnamon. Central abdomen is white, with remainder of belly buff to light brown. Feet are small, slender, and dark reddish to buffy. Tail is small, with a dingy underside. Ears are short and broad, with black edges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF54C296B74BFFF5FFC2F28BF610FBCA" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6625693" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6625693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6625693/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="119" startId="12.[105,135,3376,3397]" targetBox="[12,2748,15,3644]" targetPageId="11">
